sql:
SELECT 'Stage I' AS tumor_stage, MAX(concave_points_mean) AS max_concave_points
FROM tumor_data
WHERE tumor_stage = 'Stage I';

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM tumor_data 
WHERE class = 'Malignant' AND tumor_stage = 'Stage III';

external_knowledge:
- "Frequently watered with updates" refers to tumors with more than one update;
- "Bloomed with recent care" refers to tumors with the most recent update after January 1, 2022;
- "Mean radius" is a measure of the tumor's size;
- "Update history" includes the number of updates and the date of the last update.

- "shadows that loom large" refers to tumors;
- "kind" refers to the class of the tumor, which can be Malignant or Benign;
- "average sizes" refers to the average of the mean radius and mean area of the tumors;
- "perimeters" refers to the average of the mean perimeter of the tumors.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT tumor_stage) 
FROM tumor_data 
WHERE lymph_node_status = 'Positive';

external_knowledge:
- "Average size" refers to the average radius of the tumor;
- "Average texture" refers to the average texture of the tumor;
- "Blooms of Malignant and Benign" refers to the two classes of tumors: Malignant and Benign.

- "blooming with recent changes" refers to tumors that have had any updates or version changes;
- "logs" refer to audit trail entries for the tumors;
- "gardeners with the key to the greenhouse" refers to users with read-write permissions.

- "Gardeners" refers to users in the system;
- "Tended to the records of the tumors" refers to the log entries in the audit trails related to tumor data updates;
- "Level of access" refers to the permission levels (read-only, read-write, admin) of the users.

- 'Gardeners' refers to users with the role of 'oncologist';
- 'Logs' refers to entries in the audit trails;
- 'Weeds' refers to tumors;
- 'Size of the weeds' refers to the mean radius of the tumors.

- 'Malignant' tumors are cancerous and can spread to other parts of the body;
- 'Stage III' indicates a more advanced stage of the tumor, often requiring aggressive treatment;
- 'Concave points' are a characteristic feature of tumors that can help in distinguishing between benign and malignant tumors.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM tumor_data
WHERE radius_worst > (SELECT AVG(radius_worst) FROM tumor_data);

external_knowledge:
- 'Recently updated' refers to updates made on or after January 1, 2020;
- 'Common size category' means there are more than 10 tumors of that size;
- 'Active users' refers to users with more than 5 log entries;
- 'Read-write permissions' are determined by the `permission_level` in the `access_control` table.

sql:
SELECT MAX(CountOfTumors) AS HighestCount
FROM (
  SELECT COUNT(tumor_id) AS CountOfTumors
  FROM tumor_data
  GROUP BY tumor_stage
) AS TumorCounts;

external_knowledge:
- 'Whispers of change' refers to the `update_description` of the most recent updates;
- 'Healers of the tumors' refers to users with the role of 'oncologist';
- 'Tumors' are identified by `tumor_id`.
